comment.text: This translation key "MoveToTrash" is used to display the label for a button or option that moves an item to the trash. In a delete confirmation dialog, it appears as the title of the modal header, prompting the user to move the selected item to the trash instead of deleting it permanently.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao word 'ກະບະຕຸກ' (kabatuk) is generally understood as 'trash bin' or 'rubbish bin', but 'ກະບະ' (kaba) alone often means 'basket' or 'container'. While not strictly incorrect, 'ກະບະຕຸກ' might be perceived as slightly awkward or overly literal.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using a more common and natural phrasing like 'ຖິ້ມສູ່ກະບະຂີ້ເຫຍື້ອ' (thim su kabakhiuea) which translates to 'move to rubbish bin'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Romanian translation "Mutare în coșul de gunoi" is a literal translation but not the most natural phrasing. "Move to Trash" is typically translated as "Ștergere în coșul de gunoi" or simply "Mutare la gunoi" in Romanian user interfaces.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using "Ștergere în coșul de gunoi" or "Mutare la gunoi".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'හැලලි කූඩයට යවන්න' is a literal translation of 'Send to junk box' rather than 'Move to Trash'. It doesn't accurately convey the meaning of the English phrase.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: A more accurate translation would be 'දුල්ලකට යවන්න' (dullaka yavanna) or 'ගබඩා කුඩාට යවන්න' (gabada kudata yavanna).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian (Cyrillic) translation 'Премести у корпу' doesn't perfectly capture the meaning of 'Move to Trash'. 'Корпу' refers to a container or basket, while 'Trash' implies a designated area for discarded items. A more accurate translation would better reflect this.

The Serbian translation 'Premesti u korpu' literally translates to 'Move to bin'. While 'bin' and 'trash' are sometimes used interchangeably, 'trash' is more common and conveys the intended meaning more accurately.
The Turkish translation "Çöpe taşı" translates literally to "Carry to trash". While understandable, a more idiomatic and common translation for "Move to Trash" would be "Çöpe taşı".
